# Client state management (Zustand vs providers)

**Doctrine:** If this rule and `AGENTS.md` diverge, follow `AGENTS.md`.

**Related:** `shell-directory.mdc` (shell wiring) ¬∑ `components2-directory.mdc` (naming) ¬∑ `frontend-quality-contract.mdc` ¬ß7 ¬∑ [Zustand Next.js guide](https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand/blob/main/docs/learn/guides/nextjs.md)

---

## Prime directive

```txt
Server plane (RSC, Server Actions, #lib/auth)  ‚Üí  no Zustand, no client hooks
Client Afenda UI state                         ‚Üí  Zustand in components2/stores/
Third-party + server‚Üíclient + rare Zustand     ‚Üí  React providers in components2/providers/
```

**Refined rule:** Use **Zustand without a Provider** for shared **client-only UI** state. Use **React providers** for **third-party context**, **serializable server props**, and **Zustand store instances** only when you need per-subtree or per-request isolation (rare).

**Not true:** ‚ÄúIf Zustand exists, never use a provider.‚Äù Providers and Zustand solve different problems; both are first-class.

---

## Two planes

| Plane | Owns | Tools |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Server** | Session, tenant, org, permissions, ERP reads, mutations | RSC `layout.tsx` / `page.tsx`, Server Actions, `#lib/auth`, `#features/*` |
| **Client** | Interaction, chrome toggles, persisted UX prefs, client async | `"use client"`, Zustand, providers, TanStack Query, `useActionState` |

React Server Components are **not** ‚Äúbackend‚Äù in a separate runtime sense‚Äîthey are the **server authority boundary**. Client islands must not own tenant truth.

---

## Zustand (`components2/stores/`)

### Default pattern (current shell stores)

Module-level `create()` stores ‚Äî **no `<Provider>` wrapper**:

- Import `useAppShellStore` (etc.) from `#app-shell/client` or `#components2/stores`
- Files must start with `"use client"`
- **Never** import stores from RSC files or `#app-shell` (server-only barrel)

**Current stores (keep module singleton ‚Äî KISS/YAGNI):**

| Store | File | Role |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `useAppShellStore` | `app-shell.store.ts` | Command palette, density, rail mode preference, theme mirror |
| `useUtilityBarStore` | `utility-bar.store.ts` | Utility bar icon order (persist) |
| `useLaneMemoryStore` | `lane-memory.store.ts` | Lane memory pins (persist) |
| `useOperationalScopeUiStore` | `operational-scope.store.ts` | Scope popover UI |

### When module singleton is OK (Afenda default)

- State is **client-only** (never read/written during RSC render)
- No **request-scoped secrets** or per-user authoritative data
- Hydration-safe defaults (`commandOpen: false`, etc.) or `persist` with client-only rehydration
- Official Zustand note: module state is compatible with App Router **server caching** when RSC never touches the store

### When to add `createStore` factory + Provider (rare)

Per [Zustand Next.js guide](https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand/blob/main/docs/learn/guides/nextjs.md):

- Store seeded from **RSC props** and must not leak across requests
- Store must **reset** when leaving a route segment
- Test isolation needs a **fresh store per subtree**

**Layout:**

- Factory: `components2/stores/<domain>.store.ts` (`createStore` / `createXStore(init)`)
- Provider: `components2/providers/<domain>-store-provider.client.tsx`
- Compose in `app-shell-providers.client.tsx` only if shell-wide

Do **not** migrate existing four shell stores to this pattern without a concrete requirement.

